comment: Extension by continuity. Theorem 2 of [BourbakiTop1] p. II.20. Given an uniform space on a set ` X ` , a subset ` A ` dense in ` X ` , and a function ` F ` uniformly continuous from ` A ` to ` Y ` , that function can be extended by continuity to the whole ` X ` , and its extension is uniformly continuous. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 25-Jan-2018.)
